model: Floor One S5 Smart Wet/Dry Vac
seo_keywords: Tineco S5 dirty water tank error

problems.title: Dirty Water Tank Full (False Alarm)
problems.description: Vacuum stops and asks to empty tank, but it's not full.
possible_causes: Short circuit from water on contacts
solution_steps: Clean the metal prongs inside the dirty water tank.
Wipe the contacts on the machine body where the tank sits.

faqs.question: Is it worth fixing the issue on a Floor One S5 Smart Wet/Dry Vac?
faqs.answer: Yes. A replacement part typically costs significantly less than a new $365 vacuum, and extending the life of your Tineco is eco-friendly.

faqs.question: How do I know if my Floor One S5 Smart Wet/Dry Vac needs a new part?
faqs.answer: Common signs include reduced performance and the device failing to complete a cleaning cycle.

faqs.question: Can I replace the part on my Floor One S5 Smart Wet/Dry Vac myself?
faqs.answer: Yes, this is a user-serviceable repair. Most replacements generally require just a screwdriver and about 10-20 minutes of time.
